    "recap_headline": "University of Alabama at Birmingham Athletics",
    "recap_text": "GREENVILLE, N.C.\n\u2013 UAB Baseball (14-10, 1-2) took the series finale over East Carolina (15-9-1, 2-1) on Sunday afternoon by a score of 11-4. The win for the Blazers is their second in Greenville all-time, and their first since 2003.\nFor the third straight game, UAB got out front first in the first inning. The Blazers got the action started with two outs in the inning thanks to back-to-back walks.\nBrady Waugh\nsingled through the right side to score\nLandon Beaver\nto put UAB up, 1-0.\nFour more runs would cross for the Green and Gold in the second inning.\nWesley Helms\nled the inning off with a solo shot for his fourth home run of the season. The Blazers would take advantage of back-to-back hitters who were hit by pitches which would bring up\nJohn Paul Head\n. Head doubled to left to bring around\nBaylor Roberts\nto put runners on the corners. After a walk to load the bases,\nKevin Hall Jr.\nwould scamper home on a wild pitch which would leave runners on second and third.\nAlex Dupuy\ngrounded out to score Head to cap off the 4-run inning.\nECU would get a run back in the bottom of the second and capitalize on a leadoff walk. With runners on second and third, Walker Barron hit a sac fly to score Davin Whitaker to cut the Blazer lead to 5-1.\nThe Pirates would push another run across in the bottom of the fourth. Davin Whitaker would score off his leadoff triple courtesy of a Blazer miscue in the next at bat to trim the deficit to three.\nUAB would add back to its lead in the top of the fifth. After a hit by pitch and a double, the Blazers would have runners on second and third with nobody out.\nWesley Helms\npicked up his second RBI of the day on a groundout that scored\nBrady Waugh\nto give UAB a 6-2 lead.\nECU got a single tally in the bottom of the sixth inning. Grady Lenahan hit a solo home run for his fourth of the year to cut the UAB lead to 6-3.\nThe Green and Gold would begin to salt the game away in the top of the seventh inning by scoring three runs. The first two runs were scored on back-to-back pitches thanks to squeeze bunts by\nBaylor Roberts\nand\nKevin Hall Jr.\nJohn Paul Head\nalso singled home Roberts to give UAB a 9-3 lead.\nThe Pirates again got a single run in the bottom of the eighth. Two doubles, one by Davin Whitaker and Grady Lenahan pushed the fourth run across for East Carolina.\nMinutes after robbing a home run,\nJohn Paul Head\nhit his own 2-run home run to add to the UAB advantage. The home run was Head's 13th of the season which leads the American Conference.\nBrendan Conner\npitched the final 3.1 innings, allowed one earned run, struck out two, and capped off the Blazer victory, 11-4.\nNOTES\n-\nJohn Paul Head\nrecorded his seventh multi-hit game of the season and his sixth 3-hit game. Additionally, Head tallied his sixth multi-RBI game, tying him with\nBrady Waugh\nfor most on the team.\n-\nAndrew Hunt\n(7th) and\nWesley Helms\n(6th) also picked up multi-hit games.\n- Helms recorded his fourth multi-RBI game. Helms also extended his on-base streak to 11 games.\n-\nBaylor Roberts\nextended his on-base streak to 14 games.\n- All 14 of UAB's wins this season have come when it scores eight or more runs.\n- Sunday's game was the ninth game this season in which the Blazer offense totaled 10 hits or more.\n- The Blazer pitching staff held down an ECU offense that scored 18 runs on Saturday. On Sunday, four UAB arms combined to allow four runs on five hits en route to the victory.\n- Sunday's game was also the 20th game this season in which the UAB defense surrendered one error or less.\nUAB returns home on Tuesday as the Blazers host Jacksonville State. First pitch from Young Memorial Field is slated for 5 p.m. on ESPN+.\nFOLLOW THE BLAZERS\nFor more information on the UAB Baseball team, follow @UAB_Baseball on X and Instagram.\nCompetitive Excellence Fund\nIn the current landscape of college athletics, the Competitive Excellence Fund has become integral in our department's mission to Win Champions, Graduate with Honors, and Impact the community. Through your generosity, our coaches will have the greatest opportunity to recruit, retain, and resource talented student athletes worthy of wearing a UAB uniform.\nClick here\nor connect with Blazer Boosters on how you can continue to fuel success.",
